The Dutch hospital system reported the sharpest single-day decrease in Covid-19 patients since the figure was reported regularly by the LCPS starting in April 2020. Hospitals in the Netherlands were treating 1,398 patients with Covid-19 on Saturday. In "Breaking News" There were 1,952 people with Covid-19 in Dutch hospitals on Tuesday afternoon, the highest total since December 29. The patient tally increased ten days straight. In "Breaking News" For the first time since March 5, there was a decline in the number of Covid-19 patients in active care in Dutch hospitals. In "Breaking News" Receive top breaking news, events, ideas, and more!